laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged and fluid-filled measuring up to 1 cm. There is slightly increased density of the periappendiceal fat suggesting mild fat stranding. No free fluid within the pelvis. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and distal ureters are all within normal limits. There is no evidence of perforation.
